dialogueText.dialogue:
 You talk strangely, and run great Lengths;
I hope our Principles are not chargeable at this
Rate?

 I have heard them often say, that Men will
be damned for not believing and rejecting Christ;
and for not being converted to God.

 You are still for exalting Man, and laying
stress upon his Righteousness and good Works;
whereas all our Righteousness is as filthy Rags;
and I expect to be saved only for the
Righteousness of Christ imputed to me and received by
Faith.
